<subSubSection pageId="276" pageNumber="881" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6888637" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6888637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6888637/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="276" pageNumber="881" startId="276.[731,903,1673,1707]" targetBox="[116,707,1332,1745]" targetPageId="276">
<paragraph blockId="276.[731,1323,1319,1746]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,907,1673,1707]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from type locality on NE Luzon I, N Philippines.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="276" pageNumber="881" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="276.[117,1323,1751,2219]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[119,368,1751,1785]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 105 mm, tail 79 mm, hindfoot 23 mm, ear 10 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Luzon Shrew Mouse is small and characterized by small eyes, grayish brown relatively spiny dorsal pelage, and gray venter. Tail is shorter than head-body length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[119,1209,1909,1943]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="276.[117,1323,1751,2219]" box="[119,1209,1909,1943]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[119,229,1909,1943]" pageId="276" pageNumber="881">Habitat.</emphasis>
Secondary lowland forest at an elevation of 300 m (single specimen).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
